        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void init_uart</definition>
        <argsstring>()</argsstring>
        <name>init_uart</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Initializes the UART peripheral for standard output. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function configures the UART hardware for standard output depending on the platform-specific macros defined at compile time. If STDOUT_IS_16550 is defined, it sets the baud rate and line control register for the 16550 UART. If STDOUT_IS_PS7_UART is defined, it assumes the PS7 UART is already configured by the bootrom or BSP.</para><para>Platform-specific configuration:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>For 16550 UART: Sets baud rate and data bits.</para></listitem><listitem><para>For PS7 UART: No action required (pre-configured). </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
